Joshua Hernandez / on 8/29/2013 at 2:30pm I spoke to Mr Prashant Bhatt .
Michael. Lai.  Owner, came. Le. The manager.

At time of inspection I spoke to manager Mr. Oz in English. Note this is establishment is located on the third floor of mentioned address. Said person did not have roster of bicycles operators, information was on computer I informed said person to print documents out for future inspections as required for compliance. None of the delivery cyclists (MESSENGERS) were on site therefore complete inspection could not be done. This location may require another inspection to determine actual compliance.

At Time Of Inspection I Spoke To Employee  ( Name Not Given) who stated business uses external delivery services  (Postmates) for deliveries. Mention person stated that most of the deliveries he saw were picked up  by delivery person using cars. I then asked was there a Tablet or other device provided by Postmate to confirm these deliveries were being made by a 3rd party delivery service. He stated that the orders were placed when the delivery person came into the establishment using their phone

New business at same location,Fun City seafood restaurant.I poke with owner Mr. Small Sr. In English during inspection. Business uses third party services(ubereats and seamlees)and I explained how the business would be responsible on third party bicycle operator infractions, Mr. Small was understanding on A.C. 10-157;however business had other necessary documents if they should fall back on to in house bicyclists. Inspection took time waiting for owner to be available from a business phone call.

Spoke to Shimon in English during inspection. He stated the business doesn't make deliveries by bicycle yet but may in the future. I witnessed a delivery being by a bike operator in the area with the name of the business on his vest that marched the business. When brought up to manager he stated the bike operator is from the sister business with the same name. When checked in the app the sister business was cited by other inspector for not being in compliance. Keep eye on business in the future.

Upon conducting short surveillance prior to entering establishment I witnessed a delivery being made. Upon entering business I was told that the last inspector told that they don't deliver by bike so why am I there. I explained that I witnessed commercial bicyclist leaving. I was then told that the cyclist is from another and does deliveries for this businesses from time to time. I explained that since this business benefits from the delivery that they are responsible for compliance Jose Ortega.
